                            <comment id="13003501" author="ryantxu" created="Mon, 7 Mar 2011 18:43:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;adding test and patch from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1553&quot; title=&quot;extended dismax query parser&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-1553&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-1553&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13003505" author="ryantxu" created="Mon, 7 Mar 2011 18:47:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;From: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1553?focusedCommentId=12994448&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-12994448&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1553?focusedCommentId=12994448&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-12994448&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adding:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Make sure the &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Boolean&lt;/span&gt; Query actually has somethign there
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;( parsedUserQuery &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;instanceof&lt;/span&gt; BooleanQuery ) {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;( ((BooleanQuery)parsedUserQuery).getClauses().length &amp;lt; 1 ) {
    parsedUserQuery = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;;
  }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;seems to fix thigns.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t understand the bigger picture well enough to know the implications&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13020523" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sat, 16 Apr 2011 02:36:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a draft patch that takes the more direct approach of actually checking if the field name of a fielded query exists.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13020545" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sat, 16 Apr 2011 03:12:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One problem with the previous approach of checking for a zero length query is that it wouldn&apos;t handle cases like&lt;br/&gt;
I loved Terminator 2: Judgement Day&lt;br/&gt;
Because that gets truncated to (Terminator Day) which isn&apos;t zero length.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13020546" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sat, 16 Apr 2011 03:16:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s an updated patch with tests (both from Ryan&apos;s patch and my own additions).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13020633" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sat, 16 Apr 2011 17:24:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed to trunk &amp;amp; 3x&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13157880" author="thetaphi" created="Sun, 27 Nov 2011 12:38:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk cose after release of 3.2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13164923" author="mwatts" created="Thu, 8 Dec 2011 01:55:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This seems to give up support for &apos;&lt;em&gt;query&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
{!parser p1=v1 ... pn=vn}
&lt;p&gt;&apos;. Is this intended? (as far as I know, this would decrease the expressiveness of edismax)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13164924" author="mwatts" created="Thu, 8 Dec 2011 01:56:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;(Sorry, I&apos;m not familiar with the Jira syntax, there should be underscores on the extremes of &apos;query&apos;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13164930" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Thu, 8 Dec 2011 02:07:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmmm, you&apos;re right... this was definitely not intended.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13164978" author="mwatts" created="Thu, 8 Dec 2011 04:18:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I guess &amp;#95;val&amp;#95; is another &apos;special&apos; field to account for. Does anyone know of any others?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
